cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on energy efficient routing protocols for Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs), which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses cluster-based routing protocols, which are related to distributed and cluster computing. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with hierarchal routing protocols, which involve multiple agents working together to optimize network performance. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses how to optimize the lifetime of network nodes, which is related to control and management of systems. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves analyzing the performance of routing protocols, which can be related to information theory and communication systems.
